t: Preserve*p me, O God: for in thee do I put my trust.
O*p my soul, thou hast said unto the Lord,*s Thou art my Lord: my goodness extendeth not to thee;
But*p to the saints that are in the earth, and to the excellent, in whom is all my delight.
Their*p sorrows shall be multiplied that hasten after another god: their drink offerings of blood will I not offer, nor take up their names into my lips.
The*p Lord*s is the portion of mine inheritance and of my cup: thou maintainest my lot.
The*p lines are fallen unto me in pleasant places; yea, I have a goodly heritage.
I*p will bless the Lord,*s who hath given me counsel: my reins also instruct me in the night seasons.
I*p have set the Lord*s always before me: because he is at my right hand, I shall not be moved.
Therefore*p my heart is glad, and my glory rejoiceth: my flesh also shall rest in hope.
For*p thou wilt not leave my soul in hell; neither wilt thou suffer thine Holy One to see corruption.
Thou*p wilt shew me the path of life: in thy presence is fulness of joy; at thy right hand there are pleasures for evermore.
